trussoptimizater.Elements
Class Bar

java.lang.Object
  java.util.Observable
      trussoptimizater.Elements.Element
          trussoptimizater.Elements.Bar
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.util.Observer
public class Bar
extends Element
implements java.util.Observer

This class represents a an element connecting two nodes. This class can be used in the two following cases

  • Bar - pinned-pinned restraint - only model axial force
  • Beam - fixed - fixed restraint - model axial force, bending and shear

getMaxStress

public double[] getMaxStress()
Returns the maximum stress allowed in this bar depending on section dimensions

Uses formula stress = F/A + My/I

  • F - axial Force
  • A - cross sectional area of section
  • M - Moment at node
  • y - distance to neutral axis
  • I - Second moment of area of section

Assumes section is symmetrical

Returns:
maximum allowed stress in KN/mm^2

getMinStress

public double[] getMinStress()
Returns the minimum stress allowed in this bar depending on section dimensions

Uses formula stress = F/A - My/I

  • F - axial Force
  • A - cross sectional area of section
  • M - Moment at node
  • y - distance to neutral axis
  • I - Second moment of area of section

Assumes section is symmetrical

Returns:
minimum allowed stress in KN/mm^2
